{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17599537","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17599537"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:56:03+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:56:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15577"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15577","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15577"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8268"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70163"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8268","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8268"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15577"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55626"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"7005"},{"type":"tags","id":"8705"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19972"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19975"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70163","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70163"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe thyroid gland develops from endodermal tissue at the base of the tongue and undergoes a complex process of migration and maturation during embryological development.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the timeline of thyroid gland development?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Thyroid hormone synthesis at 7 weeks and definitive shape at 11 weeks","Both hormone synthesis and definitive shape at 7 weeks","Both hormone synthesis and definitive shape at 11 weeks","Definitive shape at 7 weeks and hormone synthesis at 11 weeks","Definitive shape at 11 weeks and hormone synthesis at 14 weeks"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe thyroid gland follows a precise developmental timeline. \u003Cstrong\u003EThyroid hormone synthesis at 7 weeks and definitive shape at 11 weeks\u003C/strong\u003E reverses the correct sequence. \u003Cstrong\u003EBoth hormone synthesis and definitive shape at 7 weeks\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as hormone synthesis occurs later. \u003Cstrong\u003EBoth hormone synthesis and definitive shape at 11 weeks\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as the gland reaches its final position earlier.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe correct sequence is \u003Cstrong\u003Edefinitive shape at 7 weeks and hormone synthesis at 11 weeks\u003C/strong\u003E. By week 7, the thyroid gland has completed its migration from the foramen caecum to its final position in the anterior neck and achieved its characteristic butterfly shape. The onset of thyroid hormone synthesis occurs at approximately week 11 when the follicular cells have matured.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDefinitive shape at 11 weeks and hormone synthesis at 14 weeks\u003C/strong\u003E occurs too late in development.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe thyroid gland develops from an endodermal outpouching called the thyroid diverticulum. It descends along the thyroglossal duct, which usually degenerates. Persistence of the thyroglossal duct can lead to thyroglossal cysts or ectopic thyroid tissue.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The thyroid gland migrates from the foramen caecum to its final position in the anterior neck by week 7 of embryological development","Thyroid follicular cells begin synthesising thyroid hormones at week 11 of embryological development","The thyroid gland develops from an endodermal outpouching at the base of the tongue"],"references":["Moran C, Schoenmakers N, Visser WE, Schoenmakers E, Agostini M, Chatterjee K. Genetic disorders of thyroid development, hormone biosynthesis and signalling. Clin Endocrinol (Oxf). 2022 Oct;97(4):502-514. doi: 10.1111/cen.14817. Epub 2022 Sep 5. PMID: 35999191; PMCID: PMC9544560","Rosen RD, Sapra A. Embryology, Thyroid. [Updated 2023 May 1]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK551611/","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewart, P. M. (Eds.). (2011). Oxford textbook of endocrinology and diabetes. Oxford University Press. USA"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55626"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15577"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55626","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55626"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-13T20:22:20+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-13T20:23:51+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8268"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70163"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.eme